  "archetype_name": "Family Weekend Showstopper: Indian Feast Night",
  "name": "Tandoori Whole Chicken with Saffron Almond Pulao and Mint-Cucumber Raita",
  "description": "A showstopping family feast: oven-roasted tandoori whole chicken served with fragrant saffron almond basmati pulao and a cool mint-cucumber yoghurt raita, with garlic naan warmed to finish.",
  "servings": "Serves 4–6",
  "prep_steps": [
    "Preheat oven to 220°C/425°F. Line a roasting tray with foil and set a rack on top.",
    "In a bowl, whisk yoghurt, tikka paste, tikka spice blend, garam masala, turmeric powder, paprika, chili flakes, crushed garlic, lemon juice, salt, and oil to make the marinade.",
    "Pat the whole chicken dry with paper towels and make shallow slashes in the thick parts of the legs and breast.",
    "Rinse basmati rice under cold water until it runs clear; soak in water for 20 minutes, then drain.",
    "Warm milk slightly and crumble saffron into it; set aside to bloom.",
    "Slice onions thinly for the rice; roughly chop mint; grate or finely chop cucumber for raita.",
    "Roughly chop almonds."
  ],
  "cook_steps": [
    "Rub the marinade all over and under the skin of the whole chicken. Place on the rack and let it sit 30–60 minutes (room temperature) or refrigerate up to 2 hours.",
    "Roast the chicken at 220°C/425°F for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 180°C/350°F and continue roasting 45–55 minutes, until juices run clear. Rest 10–15 minutes before carving.",
    "While the chicken roasts, heat ghee in a heavy pot over medium. Add bay leaves, cinnamon, cloves, and cardamom; fry until fragrant (30 seconds).",
    "Add sliced onions and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring, until deep golden (8–10 minutes).",
    "Stir in drained basmati rice and a pinch of salt; cook 1 minute to coat.",
    "Add water, saffron milk, and peas. Bring to a boil, reduce to low, cover, and cook 12 minutes. Remove from heat and rest covered 10 minutes.",
    "Fluff the rice, fold in chopped almonds, and adjust salt.",
    "For raita: In a bowl, mix yoghurt, grated cucumber, chopped mint, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Warm garlic naan bread in the oven for 3–4 minutes before serving.",
    "Carve the tandoori chicken. Serve with saffron almond pulao, mint-cucumber raita, and warm garlic naan."
  ],
